S. Africa Train Collision Injured 852, No Fatalities, SAPA Says

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-05-21T13:25:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-21/s-africa-train-collision-injured-852-no-fatalities-sapa-says.html
The number of people reported injured
in a May 19 collision between two trains in Soweto, near
Johannesburg, rose to 852, the South African Press Association
said, citing city emergency services spokesman Synock Matobako.  Injuries ranged from spinal trauma to minor fractures, the
Johannesburg-based  news agency  said, adding that the cause of
the accident is still being investigated. No one died in the
crash, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net . 